# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Crawl – environment variable template
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in real values.
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# NEVER commit .env – it is listed in .gitignore.
#
# How to obtain Google Maps API keys:
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#   2. Create or select a project.
#   3. Enable "Maps SDK for Android" and/or "Maps SDK for iOS".
#   4. Create an API key under APIs & Services → Credentials.
#   5. Restrict the key to the appropriate platform for security.
#
# These variables are read by app.config.js at build / prebuild time.
# They are embedded into the native project (Info.plist / AndroidManifest.xml)
# and are NOT bundled into the JavaScript layer.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_IOS=AIzaSyAJHO_TzJh9o-hS4-bjf-0EIab93SwNGqs
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY_ANDROID=AIzaSyAJHO_TzJh9o-hS4-bjf-0EIab93SwNGqs
